item.title: Warden, officer stabbed in prison riot
item.description: Inmates at a southern Alabama prison stabbed their warden and a correctional officer, set fire in a hallway and posted pictures of the mayhem on social media during a riot on Friday night, authorities said.

item.title: Snow machiner hits Iditarod teams
item.description: A dog competing in the Iditarod in Alaska was killed and several others were injured when a man on a snow machine allegedly hit two of the teams in the famed trail race.

item.title: Rubio picks up D.C. delegates
item.description: Hillary Clinton has won the first-ever Northern Mariana Islands Democratic caucuses, according to final results from the local Democratic Party. Ted Cruz, meanwhile, picked up a delegate in Guam, but the state's other five delegates remain uncommitted.

item.title: 'I'll file charges,' Trump says after day of disruptions
Opinion: Trump's free-speech lesson
item.description: Marc Randazza says Donald Trump, who has talked about curtailing First Amendment protections, deserves the right to speak freely under our system

item.title: The week in politics
item.description: Take a look at the week in politics from March 6 through March 12.

item.title: The week in 32 photos
Penguin returns to human friend
item.description: A heartwarming story circulating on social media tells of a penguin who swims 5,000 miles every year to see the man who saved his life. While there is some truth behind it, it's also filled with plenty of misinformation. A biologist who documented the penguin sets the record straight.

item.title: 'Different is brilliant'
At least 6 skiers killed in avalanche
item.description: A massive avalanche struck Saturday morning in the Italian Alps, sweeping away and burying about 10 skiers -- killing at least six of them, state news reported.

item.title: Goodbye to Nancy Reagan
item.description: Photos from the funeral of former first lady Nancy Reagan

item.title: Sasha and Malia Obama: The White House years
item.description: See pictures of first daughters Sasha and Malia Obama through the years since their father was elected president in 2008.

item.title: Watch: Protester rushes Ohio stage
item.description: Republican presidential hopeful Donald Trump was swarmed by security after he was startled by a protester during an event in Ohio.

item.title: Sanders: Don't blame my supporters
item.description: Bernie Sanders said Saturday that his supporters were not to blame for the unrest that led to the cancellation of a Donald Trump rally in Chicago, instead blaming the Republican front-runner for encouraging violence.

item.title: Opinion: Behind Clinton's 'cheap shot'
item.description: Words matter, whether they're offered by the candidates or the endless legion of kibitzers, like myself, who add their voices to the cacophonous pageant of democracy.

item.title: Longboarder tumbles over cliff
item.description: A longboarder was able to survive a fall that sent him tumbling off a cliff in El Paso, Texas.

item.title: 1 dead, 2 missing in tugboat crash
item.description: A tugboat struck a construction barge on the Hudson River near New York's Tappan Zee Bridge early Saturday, killing one crew member and leaving two others missing, authorities said.

item.title: Escapee's sister detained
item.description: The second of two escaped inmates was captured Saturday afternoon in Albuquerque, New Mexico, following the overnight arrest of the first fugitive, police said.

item.title: Singer sorry for Bataclan claim
item.description: Eagles of Death Metal frontman Jesse Hughes has apologized to the "people of France" for his "absurd accusations" that guards at Paris' Bataclan theater may have been involved in November's terrorist massacre during a concert by the American rock band.

item.title: Iron Maiden's plane, truck collide
item.description: Iron Maiden's personal Boeing 747 collided with a tow truck Saturday at an airport in Chile, causing major damage to the aircraft and injuring two airport workers on the ground, the band said.

item.title: Officials: Chemical attack in Iraq
item.description: Suspected terrorists with links to ISIS on Saturday fired rockets containing unspecified chemical substances into a residential part of the northern Iraqi town of Taza, Iraqi security officials told CNN.

item.title: Belfast bombing stirs fear of more
item.description: A 45-year-old man appeared in a Northern Ireland court Saturday in connection with a bombing in Belfast -- a blast that authorities fear could be one of many leading up to an uprising's milestone anniversary.

item.title: California's 'Big One': Even bigger?
item.description: The San Andreas Fault has an infamous reputation, but there are other fault lines lying around California that can trigger a powerful earthquake, especially if they rupture simultaneously, a new report says.

item.title: Trump responds
item.description: GOP front-runner Donald Trump spoke to CNN's Don Lemon about the skirmishes at his rally in Chicago and his decision to cancel his event.

item.title: 'Mattress project' suit dismissed
item.description: A New York judge has dismissed a Columbia University graduate's lawsuit claiming the school allowed a woman who said he sexually assaulted her to publicly brand him a "serial rapist."
